{"thag16.3":{"thag16.3:0.1":{"pli":"Theragāthā 16.3 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Monks 16.3 ","html":"<article id='thag16.3'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thag16.3:0.2":{"pli":"Vīsatinipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twenties ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"thag16.3:0.3":{"pli":"Paṭhamavagga ","eng":"Chapter One ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thag16.3:0.4":{"pli":"Telakānittheragāthā ","eng":"Telakāni ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thag16.3:1.1":{"pli":"“Cirarattaṃ vatātāpī, ","eng":"For a long time, sadly, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:1.2":{"pli":"dhammaṃ anuvicintayaṃ; ","eng":"though I keenly contemplated the teaching, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:1.3":{"pli":"Samaṃ cittassa nālatthaṃ, ","eng":"I gained no peace of mind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:1.4":{"pli":"pucchaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇe. ","eng":"So I asked this of ascetics and brahmins: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:2.1":{"pli":"‘Ko so pāraṅgato loke, ","eng":"“Who in the world have crossed over? ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:2.2":{"pli":"ko patto amatogadhaṃ; ","eng":"Whose attainment has freedom from death as its objective? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:2.3":{"pli":"Kassa dhammaṃ paṭicchāmi, ","eng":"Whose teaching do I accept ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:2.4":{"pli":"paramatthavijānanaṃ’. ","eng":"to understand the ultimate goal? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:3.1":{"pli":"Antovaṅkagato āsi, ","eng":"I was hooked inside, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:3.2":{"pli":"macchova ghasamāmisaṃ; ","eng":"like a fish gulping bait; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:3.3":{"pli":"Baddho mahindapāsena, ","eng":"bound like the titan Vepaciti ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:3.4":{"pli":"vepacityasuro yathā. ","eng":"in Mahinda’s trap. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"Mahinda (“Great Indra”) is a name of Sakka, the nemesis of Vepaciti. "},"thag16.3:4.1":{"pli":"Añchāmi naṃ na muñcāmi, ","eng":"Dragging it along, I’m not free ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:4.2":{"pli":"asmā sokapariddavā; ","eng":"from grief and lamentation. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:4.3":{"pli":"Ko me bandhaṃ muñcaṃ loke, ","eng":"Who will free me from bonds in the world, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:4.4":{"pli":"sambodhiṃ vedayissati. ","eng":"so that I may know awakening? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:5.1":{"pli":"Samaṇaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ vā kaṃ, ","eng":"What ascetic or brahmin ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:5.2":{"pli":"ādisantaṃ pabhaṅgunaṃ; ","eng":"points out what is frail? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:5.3":{"pli":"Kassa dhammaṃ paṭicchāmi, ","eng":"Whose teaching do I accept ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:5.4":{"pli":"jarāmaccupavāhanaṃ. ","eng":"to rinse off old age and death? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:6.1":{"pli":"Vicikicchākaṅkhāganthitaṃ, ","eng":"Tied up with uncertainty and doubt, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:6.2":{"pli":"sārambhabalasaññutaṃ; ","eng":"secured by the power of aggression, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:6.3":{"pli":"Kodhappattamanatthaddhaṃ, ","eng":"stiff as a mind beset by anger; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:6.4":{"pli":"abhijappappadāraṇaṃ. ","eng":"the arrow of covetousness, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:7.1":{"pli":"Taṇhādhanusamuṭṭhānaṃ, ","eng":"propelled by the bow of craving, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:7.2":{"pli":"dve ca pannarasāyutaṃ; ","eng":"is stuck in my twice-fifteen ribcage—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The commentary explains “twice-fifteen” as the twenty kinds of substantialist view and ten kinds of wrong view. This is implausible, as it clearly has an organic sense. I count it as 24 ribs, plus two bones each for the collar-bones, the shoulder-blades, and the sternum, making thirty in total. The sternum is technically one bone, but it is divided into upper (manubrium) and lower (gladiolus) with a notch between. "},"thag16.3:7.3":{"pli":"Passa orasikaṃ bāḷhaṃ, ","eng":"see how it stands in my breast, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:7.4":{"pli":"bhetvāna yadi tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"breaking my strong heart. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:8.1":{"pli":"Anudiṭṭhīnaṃ appahānaṃ, ","eng":"Theories are not abandoned, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:8.2":{"pli":"saṅkappaparatejitaṃ; ","eng":"they are sharpened by memories and intentions; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Read <i lang='pi' translate='no'>saṅkappasara</i> per PTS for MS’s <i lang='pi' translate='no'>saṅkappapara</i>. "},"thag16.3:8.3":{"pli":"Tena viddho pavedhāmi, ","eng":"and pierced by this I tremble, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:8.4":{"pli":"pattaṃva māluteritaṃ. ","eng":"like a leaf blowing in the gale. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:9.1":{"pli":"Ajjhattaṃ me samuṭṭhāya, ","eng":"Having arisen within, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:9.2":{"pli":"khippaṃ paccati māmakaṃ; ","eng":"what belongs to me burns quickly, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:9.3":{"pli":"Chaphassāyatanī kāyo, ","eng":"in that place where the body always heads ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:9.4":{"pli":"yattha sarati sabbadā. ","eng":"with its six sense-fields of contact. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:10.1":{"pli":"Taṃ na passāmi tekicchaṃ, ","eng":"I don’t see a healer ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:10.2":{"pli":"yo metaṃ sallamuddhare; ","eng":"who can pull out my dart of doubt ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:10.3":{"pli":"Nānārajjena satthena, ","eng":"without a lance ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:10.4":{"pli":"nāññena vicikicchitaṃ. ","eng":"or some other blade. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:11.1":{"pli":"Ko me asattho avaṇo, ","eng":"Without knife or wound, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:11.2":{"pli":"Sallamabbhantarapassayaṃ; ","eng":"who will pull out this dart ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:11.3":{"pli":"Ahiṃsaṃ sabbagattāni, ","eng":"that’s stuck inside me, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:11.4":{"pli":"Sallaṃ me uddharissati. ","eng":"without harming any part of my body? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:12.1":{"pli":"Dhammappati hi so seṭṭho, ","eng":"He really would be the Lord of the Dhamma, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:12.2":{"pli":"visadosappavāhako; ","eng":"the best one to cure the damage of poison; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:12.3":{"pli":"Gambhīre patitassa me, ","eng":"when I have fallen into deep waters, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:12.4":{"pli":"thalaṃ pāṇiñca dassaye. ","eng":"he would show me his hand and the shore. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:13.1":{"pli":"Rahadehamasmi ogāḷho, ","eng":"I’ve plunged into a lake, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:13.2":{"pli":"ahāriyarajamattike; ","eng":"and I can’t wash off the mud and dirt. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:13.3":{"pli":"Māyāusūyasārambha, ","eng":"It’s full of deceit, jealousy, aggression, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:13.4":{"pli":"thinamiddhamapatthaṭe. ","eng":"and dullness and drowsiness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:14.1":{"pli":"Uddhaccameghathanitaṃ, ","eng":"Like a thundering cloud of restlessness, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:14.2":{"pli":"saṃyojanavalāhakaṃ; ","eng":"like a stormcloud of fetters; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:14.3":{"pli":"Vāhā vahanti kuddiṭṭhiṃ, ","eng":"lustful thoughts are winds ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:14.4":{"pli":"saṅkappā rāganissitā. ","eng":"that sweep off a person with bad views. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:15.1":{"pli":"Savanti sabbadhi sotā, ","eng":"The streams flow everywhere; ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:15.2":{"pli":"latā ubbhijja tiṭṭhati; ","eng":"a weed springs up and remains. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:15.3":{"pli":"Te sote ko nivāreyya, ","eng":"Who will block the streams? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:15.4":{"pli":"taṃ lataṃ ko hi checchati. ","eng":"Who will cut the weed?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:16.1":{"pli":"Velaṃ karotha bhaddante, ","eng":"“Venerable sir, build a dam ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:16.2":{"pli":"sotānaṃ sannivāraṇaṃ; ","eng":"to block the streams. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:16.3":{"pli":"Mā te manomayo soto, ","eng":"Don’t let your mind-made streams ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:16.4":{"pli":"rukkhaṃva sahasā luve. ","eng":"cut you down suddenly like a tree.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:17.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ me bhayajātassa, ","eng":"That is how, when I was full of fear, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:17.2":{"pli":"apārā pāramesato; ","eng":"seeking the far shore from the near, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:17.3":{"pli":"Tāṇo paññāvudho satthā, ","eng":"my shelter was the teacher <j>whose weapon is wisdom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:17.4":{"pli":"isisaṅghanisevito. ","eng":"frequented by the Saṅgha of seers. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:18.1":{"pli":"Sopāṇaṃ sugataṃ suddhaṃ, ","eng":"As I was being swept away, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:18.2":{"pli":"dhammasāramayaṃ daḷhaṃ; ","eng":"he gave me a strong, simple ladder, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:18.3":{"pli":"Pādāsi vuyhamānassa, ","eng":"made of the heartwood of Dhamma, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:18.4":{"pli":"‘mā bhāyī’ti ca mabravi. ","eng":"and he said to me: “Do not fear.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:19.1":{"pli":"Satipaṭṭhānapāsādaṃ, ","eng":"I climbed the tower of mindfulness meditation, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:19.2":{"pli":"āruyha paccavekkhisaṃ; ","eng":"and checked back down ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:19.3":{"pli":"Yaṃ taṃ pubbe amaññissaṃ, ","eng":"at people delighting in substantial reality, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:19.4":{"pli":"sakkāyābhirataṃ pajaṃ. ","eng":"as I had obsessed over in the past. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:20.1":{"pli":"Yadā ca maggamaddakkhiṃ, ","eng":"When I saw the path, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:20.2":{"pli":"nāvāya abhirūhanaṃ; ","eng":"as I was embarking on the ship, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:20.3":{"pli":"Anadhiṭṭhāya attānaṃ, ","eng":"without fixating on the self, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:20.4":{"pli":"titthamaddakkhimuttamaṃ. ","eng":"I saw the supreme landing-place. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:21.1":{"pli":"Sallaṃ attasamuṭṭhānaṃ, ","eng":"The dart that arises in oneself, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:21.2":{"pli":"bhavanettippabhāvitaṃ; ","eng":"and that which stems from the leash to existence: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:21.3":{"pli":"Etesaṃ appavattāya, ","eng":"he taught the supreme path ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:21.4":{"pli":"desesi maggamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"for the canceling of these. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.3:22.1":{"pli":"Dīgharattānusayitaṃ, ","eng":"For a long time it had lain within me; ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:22.2":{"pli":"cirarattamadhiṭṭhitaṃ; ","eng":"for a long time it was fixed in me: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:22.3":{"pli":"Buddho mepānudī ganthaṃ, ","eng":"the Buddha cast aside the knot, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.3:22.4":{"pli":"visadosappavāhano”ti. ","eng":"curing the damage of poison. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thag16.3:22.5":{"pli":"… Telakāni thero …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thag16.4":{"thag16.4:0.1":{"pli":"Theragāthā 16.4 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Monks 16.4 ","html":"<article id='thag16.4'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thag16.4:0.2":{"pli":"Vīsatinipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twenties ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"thag16.4:0.3":{"pli":"Paṭhamavagga ","eng":"Chapter One ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thag16.4:0.4":{"pli":"Raṭṭhapālattheragāthā ","eng":"Raṭṭhapāla ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thag16.4:1.1":{"pli":"“Passa cittakataṃ bimbaṃ, ","eng":"“See this fancy puppet, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:1.2":{"pli":"arukāyaṃ samussitaṃ; ","eng":"a body built of sores, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:1.3":{"pli":"Āturaṃ bahusaṅkappaṃ, ","eng":"diseased, obsessed over, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:1.4":{"pli":"yassa natthi dhuvaṃ ṭhiti. ","eng":"in which nothing lasts at all. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:2.1":{"pli":"Passa cittakataṃ rūpaṃ, ","eng":"See this fancy figure, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:2.2":{"pli":"maṇinā kuṇḍalena ca; ","eng":"with its gems and earrings; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:2.3":{"pli":"Aṭṭhiṃ tacena onaddhaṃ, ","eng":"it is bones encased in skin, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:2.4":{"pli":"saha vatthehi sobhati. ","eng":"made pretty by its clothes. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:3.1":{"pli":"Alattakakatā pādā, ","eng":"Rouged feet ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:3.2":{"pli":"mukhaṃ cuṇṇakamakkhitaṃ; ","eng":"and powdered face ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:3.3":{"pli":"Alaṃ bālassa mohāya, ","eng":"may be enough to beguile a fool, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:3.4":{"pli":"no ca pāragavesino. ","eng":"but not a seeker of the far shore. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:4.1":{"pli":"Aṭṭhapadakatā kesā, ","eng":"Hair in eight braids ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:4.2":{"pli":"nettā añjanamakkhitā; ","eng":"and eyeshadow ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:4.3":{"pli":"Alaṃ bālassa mohāya, ","eng":"may be enough to beguile a fool, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:4.4":{"pli":"no ca pāragavesino. ","eng":"but not a seeker of the far shore. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:5.1":{"pli":"Añjanīva navā cittā, ","eng":"A rotting body all adorned ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:5.2":{"pli":"pūtikāyo alaṅkato; ","eng":"like a freshly painted makeup box ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:5.3":{"pli":"Alaṃ bālassa mohāya, ","eng":"may be enough to beguile a fool, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:5.4":{"pli":"no ca pāragavesino. ","eng":"but not a seeker of the far shore. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:6.1":{"pli":"Odahi migavo pāsaṃ, ","eng":"The hunter laid his snare, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:6.2":{"pli":"nāsadā vāguraṃ migo; ","eng":"but the deer didn’t spring the trap. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:6.3":{"pli":"Bhutvā nivāpaṃ gacchāma, ","eng":"I’ve eaten the bait and now I go, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:6.4":{"pli":"kandante migabandhake. ","eng":"leaving the trapper to lament. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:7.1":{"pli":"Chinno pāso migavassa, ","eng":"The hunter’s snare is broken, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:7.2":{"pli":"nāsadā vāguraṃ migo; ","eng":"but the deer didn’t spring the trap. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:7.3":{"pli":"Bhutvā nivāpaṃ gacchāma, ","eng":"I’ve eaten the bait and now I go, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:7.4":{"pli":"socante migaluddake. ","eng":"leaving the deer-hunter to grieve.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:8.1":{"pli":"Passāmi loke sadhane manusse, ","eng":"“I see rich people in the world who, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:8.2":{"pli":"Laddhāna vittaṃ na dadanti mohā; ","eng":"because of delusion, <j>give not the money they’ve earned. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:8.3":{"pli":"Luddhā dhanaṃ sannicayaṃ karonti, ","eng":"Greedily, they hoard their riches, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:8.4":{"pli":"Bhiyyova kāme abhipatthayanti. ","eng":"yearning for ever more sensual pleasures. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:9.1":{"pli":"Rājā pasayhappathaviṃ vijetvā, ","eng":"A king who conquered the earth by force, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:9.2":{"pli":"Sasāgarantaṃ mahimāvasanto; ","eng":"ruling the land from sea to sea, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:9.3":{"pli":"Oraṃ samuddassa atittarūpo, ","eng":"unsatisfied with the near shore of the ocean, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:9.4":{"pli":"Pāraṃ samuddassapi patthayetha. ","eng":"would still yearn for the further shore. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:10.1":{"pli":"Rājā ca aññe ca bahū manussā, ","eng":"Not just the king, but others too, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:10.2":{"pli":"Avītataṇhā maraṇaṃ upenti; ","eng":"reach death not rid of craving. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:10.3":{"pli":"Ūnāva hutvāna jahanti dehaṃ, ","eng":"They leave the body still wanting, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:10.4":{"pli":"Kāmehi lokamhi na hatthi titti. ","eng":"for in this world sensual pleasures never satisfy. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:11.1":{"pli":"Kandanti naṃ ñātī pakiriya kese, ","eng":"Relatives lament, their hair disheveled, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:11.2":{"pli":"Aho vatā no amarāti cāhu; ","eng":"saying ‘Ah! Alas! They’re not immortal!’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:11.3":{"pli":"Vatthena naṃ pārutaṃ nīharitvā, ","eng":"They take out the body wrapped in a shroud, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:11.4":{"pli":"Citaṃ samodhāya tato ḍahanti. ","eng":"heap up a pyre, and burn it there. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:12.1":{"pli":"So ḍayhati sūlehi tujjamāno, ","eng":"It’s poked with stakes while being burnt, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:12.2":{"pli":"Ekena vatthena pahāya bhoge; ","eng":"in just a single cloth, all wealth gone. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:12.3":{"pli":"Na mīyamānassa bhavanti tāṇā, ","eng":"Relatives, friends, and companions ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:12.4":{"pli":"Ñātī ca mittā atha vā sahāyā. ","eng":"can’t help you when you’re dying. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:13.1":{"pli":"Dāyādakā tassa dhanaṃ haranti, ","eng":"Heirs take your riches, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:13.2":{"pli":"Satto pana gacchati yena kammaṃ; ","eng":"while beings fare on according to their deeds. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:13.3":{"pli":"Na mīyamānaṃ dhanamanveti kiñci, ","eng":"Riches don’t follow you when you die; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:13.4":{"pli":"Puttā ca dārā ca dhanañca raṭṭhaṃ. ","eng":"nor do children, wife, wealth, nor kingdom. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:14.1":{"pli":"Na dīghamāyuṃ labhate dhanena, ","eng":"Longevity isn’t gained by riches, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:14.2":{"pli":"Na cāpi vittena jaraṃ vihanti; ","eng":"nor does wealth banish old age; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:14.3":{"pli":"Appaṃ hidaṃ jīvitamāhu dhīrā, ","eng":"for the attentive say this life is short, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:14.4":{"pli":"Asassataṃ vippariṇāmadhammaṃ. ","eng":"it’s perishable and not eternal. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:15.1":{"pli":"Aḍḍhā daliddā ca phusanti phassaṃ, ","eng":"The rich and the poor feel its touch; ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:15.2":{"pli":"Bālo ca dhīro ca tatheva phuṭṭho; ","eng":"the fool and the attentive one feel it too. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:15.3":{"pli":"Bālo hi bālyā vadhitova seti, ","eng":"But the fool lies stricken by their own folly, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:15.4":{"pli":"Dhīro ca no vedhati phassaphuṭṭho. ","eng":"while the attentive don’t tremble at the touch. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:16.1":{"pli":"Tasmā hi paññāva dhanena seyyā, ","eng":"Therefore wisdom’s much better than wealth, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:16.2":{"pli":"Yāya vosānamidhādhigacchati; ","eng":"since by wisdom <j>you reach consummation in this life. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:16.3":{"pli":"Abyositattā hi bhavābhavesu, ","eng":"But if because of delusion <j>you don’t reach consummation, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:16.4":{"pli":"Pāpāni kammāni karoti mohā. ","eng":"you’ll do evil deeds in life after life. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:17.1":{"pli":"Upeti gabbhañca parañca lokaṃ, ","eng":"One who enters a womb and the world beyond, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:17.2":{"pli":"Saṃsāramāpajja paramparāya; ","eng":"will transmigrate from one life to the next. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:17.3":{"pli":"Tassappapañño abhisaddahanto, ","eng":"While someone of little wisdom, <j>placing faith in them, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:17.4":{"pli":"Upeti gabbhañca parañca lokaṃ. ","eng":"also enters a womb and the world beyond. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:18.1":{"pli":"Coro yathā sandhimukhe gahīto, ","eng":"As a bandit caught in a window ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:18.2":{"pli":"Sakammunā haññati pāpadhammo; ","eng":"is punished for his own bad deeds; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:18.3":{"pli":"Evaṃ pajā pecca paramhi loke, ","eng":"so after departing, in the world beyond, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:18.4":{"pli":"Sakammunā haññati pāpadhammo. ","eng":"people are punished for their own bad deeds. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:19.1":{"pli":"Kāmā hi citrā madhurā manoramā, ","eng":"Sensual pleasures are diverse, sweet, delightful, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:19.2":{"pli":"Virūparūpena mathenti cittaṃ; ","eng":"appearing in disguise they disturb the mind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:19.3":{"pli":"Ādīnavaṃ kāmaguṇesu disvā, ","eng":"Seeing danger in sensual stimulations, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:19.4":{"pli":"Tasmā ahaṃ pabbajitomhi rāja. ","eng":"I went forth, O King. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:20.1":{"pli":"Dumapphalānīva patanti māṇavā, ","eng":"As fruit falls from a tree, so the sons of Manu fall, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Māṇava</i>, which normally means “Vedic student”, is occasionally used in the poetic sense of <i lang='pi' translate='no'>manussa</i> (“humans”). Both words mean “descendant of the first man, Manu”. "},"thag16.4:20.2":{"pli":"Daharā ca vuḍḍhā ca sarīrabhedā; ","eng":"young and old, when the body breaks up. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:20.3":{"pli":"Etampi disvā pabbajitomhi rāja, ","eng":"Seeing this, too, I went forth, O King; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:20.4":{"pli":"Apaṇṇakaṃ sāmaññameva seyyo. ","eng":"the ascetic life is unfailingly better.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:21.1":{"pli":"Saddhāyāhaṃ pabbajito, ","eng":"“I went forth out of faith ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:21.2":{"pli":"upeto jinasāsane; ","eng":"joining the victor’s dispensation. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:21.3":{"pli":"Avañjhā mayhaṃ pabbajjā, ","eng":"My going forth wasn’t wasted; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:21.4":{"pli":"anaṇo bhuñjāmi bhojanaṃ. ","eng":"I enjoy my food free of debt. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:22.1":{"pli":"Kāme ādittato disvā, ","eng":"I saw sensual pleasures as burning, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:22.2":{"pli":"Jātarūpāni satthato; ","eng":"gold as a cutting blade, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:22.3":{"pli":"Gabbhavokkantito dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"conception in a womb as suffering, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:22.4":{"pli":"Nirayesu mahabbhayaṃ. ","eng":"and the hells as very fearful. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:23.1":{"pli":"Etamādīnavaṃ ñatvā, ","eng":"Knowing this danger, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:23.2":{"pli":"saṃvegaṃ alabhiṃ tadā; ","eng":"I was struck with a sense of urgency. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:23.3":{"pli":"Sohaṃ viddho tadā santo, ","eng":"I was stabbed, but then I found peace, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:23.4":{"pli":"sampatto āsavakkhayaṃ. ","eng":"attaining the end of defilements. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:24.1":{"pli":"Pariciṇṇo mayā satthā, ","eng":"I’ve served the teacher ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:24.2":{"pli":"kataṃ buddhassa sāsanaṃ; ","eng":"and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:24.3":{"pli":"Ohito garuko bhāro, ","eng":"The heavy burden is laid down, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:24.4":{"pli":"bhavanetti samūhatā. ","eng":"the leash to existence is eradicated. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.4:25.1":{"pli":"Yassatthāya pabbajito, ","eng":"I’ve reached the goal ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:25.2":{"pli":"agārasmānagāriyaṃ; ","eng":"for the sake of which I went forth ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:25.3":{"pli":"So me attho anuppatto, ","eng":"from the lay life to homelessness—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.4:25.4":{"pli":"sabbasaṃyojanakkhayo”ti. ","eng":"the ending of all fetters.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thag16.4:25.5":{"pli":"… Raṭṭhapālo thero …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"thag16.5":{"thag16.5:0.1":{"pli":"Theragāthā 16.5 ","eng":"Verses of the Senior Monks 16.5 ","html":"<article id='thag16.5'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"thag16.5:0.2":{"pli":"Vīsatinipāta ","eng":"The Book of the Twenties ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"thag16.5:0.3":{"pli":"Paṭhamavagga ","eng":"Chapter One ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"thag16.5:0.4":{"pli":"Mālukyaputtattheragāthā ","eng":"Māluṅkyaputta (2nd) ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"thag16.5:1.1":{"pli":"“Rūpaṃ disvā sati muṭṭhā, ","eng":"When you see a sight, mindfulness is lost ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:1.2":{"pli":"Piyaṃ nimittaṃ manasi karoto; ","eng":"as you focus on a pleasant feature. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:1.3":{"pli":"Sārattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind full of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:1.4":{"pli":"Tañca ajjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:2.1":{"pli":"Tassa vaḍḍhanti vedanā, ","eng":"Many feelings grow ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:2.2":{"pli":"anekā rūpasambhavā; ","eng":"arising from sights. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:2.3":{"pli":"Abhijjhā ca vihesā ca, ","eng":"The mind is damaged ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:2.4":{"pli":"cittamassūpahaññati; ","eng":"by covetousness and cruelty. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:2.5":{"pli":"Evamācinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Heaping up suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:2.6":{"pli":"ārā nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be far from extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:3.1":{"pli":"Saddaṃ sutvā sati muṭṭhā, ","eng":"When you hear a sound, mindfulness is lost ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:3.2":{"pli":"Piyaṃ nimittaṃ manasi karoto; ","eng":"as you focus on a pleasant feature. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:3.3":{"pli":"Sārattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind full of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:3.4":{"pli":"Tañca ajjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:4.1":{"pli":"Tassa vaḍḍhanti vedanā, ","eng":"Many feelings grow ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:4.2":{"pli":"anekā saddasambhavā; ","eng":"arising from sounds. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:4.3":{"pli":"Abhijjhā ca vihesā ca, ","eng":"The mind is damaged ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:4.4":{"pli":"cittamassūpahaññati; ","eng":"by covetousness and cruelty. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:4.5":{"pli":"Evamācinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Heaping up suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:4.6":{"pli":"ārā nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be far from extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:5.1":{"pli":"Gandhaṃ ghatvā sati muṭṭhā, ","eng":"When you smell an odor, mindfulness is lost ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:5.2":{"pli":"Piyaṃ nimittaṃ manasi karoto; ","eng":"as you focus on a pleasant feature. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:5.3":{"pli":"Sārattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind full of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:5.4":{"pli":"Tañca ajjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:6.1":{"pli":"Tassa vaḍḍhanti vedanā, ","eng":"Many feelings grow ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:6.2":{"pli":"anekā gandhasambhavā; ","eng":"arising from smells. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:6.3":{"pli":"Abhijjhā ca vihesā ca, ","eng":"The mind is damaged ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:6.4":{"pli":"cittamassūpahaññati; ","eng":"by covetousness and cruelty. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:6.5":{"pli":"Evamācinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Heaping up suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:6.6":{"pli":"ārā nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be far from extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:7.1":{"pli":"Rasaṃ bhotvā sati muṭṭhā, ","eng":"When you enjoy a taste, mindfulness is lost ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:7.2":{"pli":"Piyaṃ nimittaṃ manasi karoto; ","eng":"as you focus on a pleasant feature. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:7.3":{"pli":"Sārattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind full of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:7.4":{"pli":"Tañca ajjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:8.1":{"pli":"Tassa vaḍḍhanti vedanā, ","eng":"Many feelings grow ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:8.2":{"pli":"anekā rasasambhavā; ","eng":"arising from tastes. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:8.3":{"pli":"Abhijjhā ca vihesā ca, ","eng":"The mind is damaged ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:8.4":{"pli":"cittamassūpahaññati; ","eng":"by covetousness and cruelty. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:8.5":{"pli":"Evamācinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Heaping up suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:8.6":{"pli":"ārā nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be far from extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:9.1":{"pli":"Phassaṃ phussa sati muṭṭhā, ","eng":"When you sense a touch, mindfulness is lost ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:9.2":{"pli":"Piyaṃ nimittaṃ manasi karoto; ","eng":"as you focus on a pleasant feature. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:9.3":{"pli":"Sārattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind full of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:9.4":{"pli":"Tañca ajjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:10.1":{"pli":"Tassa vaḍḍhanti vedanā, ","eng":"Many feelings grow ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:10.2":{"pli":"anekā phassasambhavā; ","eng":"arising from touches. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:10.3":{"pli":"Abhijjhā ca vihesā ca, ","eng":"The mind is damaged ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:10.4":{"pli":"cittamassūpahaññati; ","eng":"by covetousness and cruelty. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:10.5":{"pli":"Evamācinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Heaping up suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:10.6":{"pli":"ārā nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be far from extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:11.1":{"pli":"Dhammaṃ ñatvā sati muṭṭhā, ","eng":"When you know an idea, mindfulness is lost ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:11.2":{"pli":"Piyaṃ nimittaṃ manasi karoto; ","eng":"as you focus on a pleasant feature. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:11.3":{"pli":"Sārattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind full of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:11.4":{"pli":"Tañca ajjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:12.1":{"pli":"Tassa vaḍḍhanti vedanā, ","eng":"Many feelings grow ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:12.2":{"pli":"anekā dhammasambhavā; ","eng":"arising from ideas. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:12.3":{"pli":"Abhijjhā ca vihesā ca, ","eng":"The mind is damaged ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:12.4":{"pli":"cittamassūpahaññati; ","eng":"by covetousness and cruelty. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:12.5":{"pli":"Evamācinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Heaping up suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:12.6":{"pli":"ārā nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be far from extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:13.1":{"pli":"Na so rajjati rūpesu, ","eng":"There’s no desire for sights ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:13.2":{"pli":"rūpaṃ disvā patissato; ","eng":"when you see a sight with mindfulness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:13.3":{"pli":"Virattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind free of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:13.4":{"pli":"tañca nājjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you don’t keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:14.1":{"pli":"Yathāssa passato rūpaṃ, ","eng":"Even as you see a sight ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:14.2":{"pli":"sevato cāpi vedanaṃ; ","eng":"and undergo a feeling, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:14.3":{"pli":"Khīyati nopacīyati, ","eng":"you wear away, you don’t heap up: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:14.4":{"pli":"evaṃ so caratī sato; ","eng":"that’s how to live mindfully. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:14.5":{"pli":"Evaṃ apacinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Eroding suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:14.6":{"pli":"santike nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be in the presence of extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:15.1":{"pli":"Na so rajjati saddesu, ","eng":"There’s no desire for sounds ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:15.2":{"pli":"saddaṃ sutvā patissato; ","eng":"when you hear a sound with mindfulness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:15.3":{"pli":"Virattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind free of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:15.4":{"pli":"tañca nājjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you don’t keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:16.1":{"pli":"Yathāssa suṇato saddaṃ, ","eng":"Even as you hear a sound ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:16.2":{"pli":"sevato cāpi vedanaṃ; ","eng":"and undergo a feeling, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:16.3":{"pli":"Khīyati nopacīyati, ","eng":"you wear away, you don’t heap up: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:16.4":{"pli":"evaṃ so caratī sato; ","eng":"that’s how to live mindfully. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:16.5":{"pli":"Evaṃ apacinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Eroding suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:16.6":{"pli":"santike nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be in the presence of extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:17.1":{"pli":"Na so rajjati gandhesu, ","eng":"There’s no desire for odors ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:17.2":{"pli":"gandhaṃ ghatvā patissato; ","eng":"when you smell an odor with mindfulness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:17.3":{"pli":"Virattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind free of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:17.4":{"pli":"tañca nājjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you don’t keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:18.1":{"pli":"Yathāssa ghāyato gandhaṃ, ","eng":"Even as you smell an odor ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:18.2":{"pli":"sevato cāpi vedanaṃ; ","eng":"and undergo a feeling, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:18.3":{"pli":"Khīyati nopacīyati, ","eng":"you wear away, you don’t heap up: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:18.4":{"pli":"evaṃ so caratī sato; ","eng":"that’s how to live mindfully. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:18.5":{"pli":"Evaṃ apacinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Eroding suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:18.6":{"pli":"santike nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be in the presence of extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:19.1":{"pli":"Na so rajjati rasesu, ","eng":"There’s no desire for tastes ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:19.2":{"pli":"rasaṃ bhotvā patissato; ","eng":"when you enjoy a taste with mindfulness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:19.3":{"pli":"Virattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind free of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:19.4":{"pli":"tañca nājjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you don’t keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:20.1":{"pli":"Yathāssa sāyarato rasaṃ, ","eng":"Even as you savor a taste ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:20.2":{"pli":"sevato cāpi vedanaṃ; ","eng":"and undergo a feeling, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:20.3":{"pli":"Khīyati nopacīyati, ","eng":"you wear away, you don’t heap up: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:20.4":{"pli":"evaṃ so caratī sato; ","eng":"that’s how to live mindfully. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:20.5":{"pli":"Evaṃ apacinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Eroding suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:20.6":{"pli":"santike nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be in the presence of extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:21.1":{"pli":"Na so rajjati phassesu, ","eng":"There’s no desire for touches ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:21.2":{"pli":"phassaṃ phussa patissato; ","eng":"when you sense a touch with mindfulness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:21.3":{"pli":"Virattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind free of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:21.4":{"pli":"tañca nājjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you don’t keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:22.1":{"pli":"Yathāssa phusato phassaṃ, ","eng":"Even as you sense a touch ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:22.2":{"pli":"sevato cāpi vedanaṃ; ","eng":"and get familiar with how it feels, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:22.3":{"pli":"Khīyati nopacīyati, ","eng":"you wear away, you don’t heap up: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:22.4":{"pli":"evaṃ so caratī sato; ","eng":"that’s how to live mindfully. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:22.5":{"pli":"Evaṃ apacinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Eroding suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:22.6":{"pli":"santike nibbāna vuccati. ","eng":"you’re said to be in the presence of extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:23.1":{"pli":"Na so rajjati dhammesu, ","eng":"There’s no desire for ideas ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:23.2":{"pli":"dhammaṃ ñatvā patissato; ","eng":"when you know an idea with mindfulness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:23.3":{"pli":"Virattacitto vedeti, ","eng":"Experiencing it with a mind free of desire, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:23.4":{"pli":"tañca nājjhosa tiṭṭhati. ","eng":"you don’t keep clinging to it. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"thag16.5:24.1":{"pli":"Yathāssa vijānato dhammaṃ, ","eng":"Even as you know an idea ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:24.2":{"pli":"sevato cāpi vedanaṃ; ","eng":"and get familiar with how it feels, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:24.3":{"pli":"Khīyati nopacīyati, ","eng":"you wear away, you don’t heap up: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:24.4":{"pli":"evaṃ so caratī sato; ","eng":"that’s how to live mindfully. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:24.5":{"pli":"Evaṃ apacinato dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"Eroding suffering like this, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"thag16.5:24.6":{"pli":"santike nibbāna vuccati”. ","eng":"you’re said to be in the presence of extinguishment. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"thag16.5:24.7":{"pli":"… Mālukyaputto thero …. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}}}